<item>
            <title>[FELIX-435] StackOverflowError in URLHandlers.createStreamHandler() when creating URL on jamvm and Mika </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-435</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It looks like we have an unfortunate interaction between our ExtensionManager and the URLHandlers on jamvm and Mika . &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Basically, when a URL is created inside a bundle the URLHandlers are asked to find a stream handler. One step of this process is to do a Class.forName() which will use the framework classloader. Now, in case this happens to be a URLClassLoader we have added a URL with our ExtensionManager as a handler. This is not a problem unless the URL is toString()-ed and then recreated which seems to be the case for jamvm/classpath and Mika. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Subsequently, the attempt to find a handler for the protocol of the ExtensionManager URL will call URLHandlers.createStreamHandler() again and we have a loop until StackOverflowError. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
